<font color="#FF0000">THANK YOU</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan 29  1:07:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is a great reminder that we in SEA were only an extension<br>
of something much greater left at home. For myself, I can only remember the Dear John letter, and the letter while I was in the hospitale from the<br>
girl in the private school that first wrote how sad she was <br>
for the GI's getting hurt and then responded to my letter that <br>
she had been made to write that letter in a English class and that she realy <br>
thought we were all killers.  Then when I came back being spit on in the San Francisco airport by a long hair hippie.<br>
I wounder what banker he is now? The joy I find in this section is the love that the women left behind had for their men,<br>
and the men who stayed true to them.  I wounder if I could explaine now to such a wife how her husband got killed taking a flight over the &quot;Trail&quot;.<br>
I ask my self that question now as my daughter 12 is surprized that I fought in Vietnam. I have been to the &quot;Wall&quot; and left pictures and names of friends that never came back.<br>
Some times in the middle of a hell day I stop and listen, I realize there is no &quot;incoming&quot; and there is no real problem only learning to cope with a teenager.<br>
God bless you all, <br>
MSG DHB<br>

